cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use Hide & Seek 2.0 in your research, please cite this project as well
  as the original OpenAI work that inspired it (see `references` below).
title: "Hide & Seek 2.0: A JAX Recreation and Expansion of Emergent Tool Use"
abstract: >-
  A modern JAX/Flax recreation and expansion of OpenAI's 2019 Emergent Tool Use
  From Multi-Agent Autocurricula (Hide-and-Seek). The environment, physics, and
  MAPPO learner run end-to-end on the GPU (PureJaxRL / JaxMARL style). Version
  2.0 adds variable mass and cooperative physics, sensory decoys, fog of war and
  dynamic lighting, destructible walls and doors, and stamina, to provoke richer
  emergent tool use, deception, and teamwork. This is a research scaffold.
type: software
version: "2.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-13"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - reinforcement-learning
  - multi-agent
  - jax
  - flax
  - mappo
  - self-play
  - hide-and-seek
  - emergent-tool-use
authors:
